		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I'm with Jonwin on this. It's all about perception. If I'm rolling around with my main and see a mob I would like to take down (and considering how much those augs sell for, I'd like to take them down when I see them), I'm going to do it if I can. If I see a group there camping the spawn, I won't just rush in though. I'll ask if they're going after it, but they have a time limit. If they don't attack it after say... 10 minutes, I'm taking it. If they haven't attacked it by then, then they obviously can't handle the encounter, and therefor don't &quot;have&quot; the camp. While most people respect camps, it's also understood that if you can't handle a camp, you can't claim a camp. If they told me &quot;we're waiting on our warrior to get back, he got killed and we don't have a rezzer.&quot; then I'd give the benefit of the doubt and wait another 10 minutes or so. If they said &quot;We're looking for a warrior to tank because we can't handle it yet&quot; then they can't claim the camp.<br /><br />They may sound like a dickish thing to do to the lower guys, but respect works in both directions. If you can't handle the encounter, you can't claim it.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062&resize=true" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="ak