		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default [2.33]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=czaemon&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>from my time whoring names in bot:<br />you have eight minutes after I arrive to engage your mob.&nbsp;&nbsp;if you wipe, too bad. if fewer than two-thirds of your group is there, I'll take the mob.   if you have someone on the way to help, fine -- as long as they get there and get buffed in time.  If you wipe, I'll let the mob regen to full, and then kill it.   If you wipe, I will rez you -- after the mob is dead.  <br /><br />those were my guidelines for dealing with people I didn't know.  for people I knew/liked, I would rez you, give you as many tries as you needed, help you, whatever. <br /><br />and yes, for people I knew and didn't like, I was meaner.  You have an unengaged name and I arrive at your camp? cool.  you have fifteen seconds to engage it, or I'll take it.  If you had enough force to fulfil the 'first in force' rule, you would be able to engage it within fifteen seconds.  <br /><br />you want a bot tower?  cool.  beat me to engaging the boss.   I'll be quite happy to wait for your cleric to get a critical resist, and jump you then. got the boss to 1%, but are wiping now?  heeheehee.  I'll kill it after you die.   but then again,  I did not get along with (slight understatement..) any of the other people that routinely did towers. <br /><br />I've never been as nasty as I was to the other tower farmers, anywhere else in everquest.   we did basically anything and everything to each other to win -- at one point, one of the other enchanters went through water tower, charmed almost every elemental, buffed them, and gave them pet weaps, so they conned indiff but still saw invis.  She left one safe, convoluted path through the tower, so no one else could do the tower without clearing 40+ mobs.  I never trained anyone, but still managed to get some fat trains dumped on me.  One of other groups of farmers  buffed every elemental in the towers to the teeth, because they had an enchanter (can charm giants) and we only had a mage (elementals only.)<br /><br />Basically, the guild-wars most servers had during velious, on a slightly smaller scale, complete with venemous ninja-recruiting.<br /><br />  It's the only time in everquest I've ever stooped to charmed-pet dispelling, albeit in retaliation for a series of trains. <br /><br />we also ran amuck over tactics, I actually got one of them banned when I found her mega-exploiting faction, the gm popped in right after she finished soloing rallos zek.<br /><br />horribly violent, mean, nasty, and one of the best times I've had in EQ.  the end result?  most of us became way better players than we would have without having had essentially pvp competition.  <br /><br /><br />now that my primary gear source is not what I've farmed myself, I'm much nicer on nameds.   I mostly avoid people I have problems with now -- easier, since we aren't competing for the same eight six-hour spawn mobs.  Except A.  I think I'd dump a train in her lap if I ever saw her again.  <br /><br /> </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.czaemon.com" target="akztarg">Czaemon</a><br /></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from retired. for the summer. kind of.</td></tr></table>
