you sit there with a mob popped but not killing it is a minute longer before the next mob spawns. Since the rares are part of that cycle, one can argue that you are reducing the total number of future chances for people to get that spawn by sitting there not killing the one in front of you. That's pretty darn inconsiderate.<br /><br /><br />As several people have stated, there are no camps, but most people will respect a group that is &quot;in force&quot; and reasonably quick about engaging. This does not mean that you can &quot;call the mob&quot; and then sit there for 3 hours assembling enough people to kill it. No one's going to let you get away with that, and you are potentially screwing people over by doing it. With some mobs, the respawn is calculated in such a way that some idiot delaying 3 hours to kill it may cause the next respawn to fall outside the raid window of a group that might otherwise have been able to engage. It's *extremely* inconsiderate to sit on a spawn.<br /><br /><br />Piss or get off the pot. It is just as inconsiderate for you to sit there occupying a spawn but not killing it as it is for someone to run up and &quot;take&quot; your spawn. Seems a bit harsh, but you have to think about things from other players perspectives as well as yours.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from San Diego, CA</td></tr></table>
