		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Simple misunderstanding. A lot of people were getting stressed out over those fire hornet wings. It was stupid of him to take it to /ooc, but, what ya gonna do?<br /><br />That's a problem you're always going to have as a bard though. Most bards pull with a non-damaging song, be it dispell, slow, snare, debuff, whatever. They're very low aggro generating songs, so it's easy for the tank to take aggro, and it &quot;preps&quot; the mob for the group. The downside is it's VERY easy for another puller to snag it if they want with something as simple as 1 arrow. I've had it done to me many times. If I'm trying to pull a mob that is in high demand, say a named in WoS for instance, I'll usually grab a few adds too. If they do manage to steal my named from me before I get to camp, they're going to have to deal with the adds after I fade... hope they got a chanter. I'll be sure to watch the named mobs HP in my targeting window too. If it starts to go up, they aren't engaged anymore and it's free for the pullin'.<br /><br />There was one time when someone stole a named from me after I did a beautiful fade split in middle sands in BoT. They stole the named and dragged it to lower sands. It was SO obvious I was pulling it, I mean, I had to fade split it twice to get it single, but they stole it anyway. Normally, I would of said something to them and left it at that, but this time I was mad. It was a nice pull! So, I memmed highsun, waited for the mob to get to 10%, then gated it back. Like idiots, they ran after it, and got all of the adds that I was able to split off (a kriger and 3 or 4 regular mobs). After the groups untimely demise, I fade split the named again and we got the loot (it only dropped a freakin' ring of thunderous spirits IIRC).<br /><br />Moral of the story: if you're a bard pulling highly contested mobs, be ready to deal with aggro stealing aszhats. You're GOING to run into them.<br /><br />This may all sound like very rude behavior. Just keep in mind that I don't resort to these tactics unless someone deserves them. If I run up and someone's already engaged or pulled a named, I wouldn't do any of this to get the named. It's only if I pull a mob first and someone tries to KS me.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062&resize=true" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Monk</span></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from over the river and through the woods...</td></tr></table>
